                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 814.51/245.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé d’Affaires at
                            London</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-05-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 13, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Upon presenting the subject of Department’s telegram of the 12th instant to the
                    Foreign Office I was informed that the Guatemalan <pb facs="0674" n="570"
                        xml:id="pg_570"/> Minister for Foreign Affairs yielded yesterday to the
                    British demands and that the question is settled.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
